    "result": {"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Trails in SA"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"53933f9f-bd47-51a0-8c64-e0d6eaac35d5","excerpt":"The Kloofendal nature trail is great because you can get the feel of being far away in the outdoors but it’s actually nearby in Roodepoort Johannesburg.  The…","html":"<p>The Kloofendal nature trail is great because you can get the feel of being far away in the outdoors but it’s actually nearby in Roodepoort Johannesburg.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 400px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/trails-data/static/9957f6ffecf2a7a560a50b47c66e5380/4b190/kloofendal-nature-reserve.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"dam looking a bit low\"\n        title=\"dam looking a bit low\"\n        src=\"/trails-data/static/9957f6ffecf2a7a560a50b47c66e5380/066f9/kloofendal-nature-reserve.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/trails-data/static/9957f6ffecf2a7a560a50b47c66e5380/b9e9c/kloofendal-nature-reserve.jpg 100w,\n/trails-data/static/9957f6ffecf2a7a560a50b47c66e5380/e07e9/kloofendal-nature-reserve.jpg 200w,\n/trails-data/static/9957f6ffecf2a7a560a50b47c66e5380/066f9/kloofendal-nature-reserve.jpg 400w,\n/trails-data/static/9957f6ffecf2a7a560a50b47c66e5380/b4294/kloofendal-nature-reserve.jpg 600w,\n/trails-data/static/9957f6ffecf2a7a560a50b47c66e5380/4b190/kloofendal-nature-reserve.jpg 800w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>The entry is free and it is open from 6:00 to 18:00 and only closed if there is a fire hazard (lots of long dry grass). There is a guard at the gate to sign in and ample parking.</p>\n<p>After you’ve parked and walk into the reserve there is an amphitheatre with a large open area for you to relax and have a picnic, I saw a couple people chilling out in the sun. There are bathrooms and a couple thatched roofs for you to sit under if the sun gets hot.</p>\n<p>There are 4 routes ranging from 0.5 to 3.5 km. There is a trail for everyone here, simple, short and easy to a little harder and steeper. All of the trails I think are suitable for children and first timers. The tougher red route (Dassie) has some steep and rocky bits. The routes are well maintained with grass cut and obstacles removed.</p>\n<p>Look out for the dam and the wonderful views from the top of the hill. Also there is an old mine in the reserve but it’s closed off.</p>\n<p>No dogs allowed.</p>","fields":{"slug":"/gauteng/kloofendal-nature-reserve/","province":"gauteng"},"frontmatter":{"trailName":"Kloofendal Nature Reserve","date":"23/10/2020","location":"https://goo.gl/maps/H7YVLVPmhrVnKhdi9","routes":"https://kloofendalfriends.yolasite.com/resources/Knd_Trails.jpg","link":"https://kloofendalfriends.yolasite.com/","activity":["running","walking","hiking"],"cost":"free"}},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/gauteng/kings-kloof/"},"frontmatter":{"title":""}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/western-cape/lions-head/"},"frontmatter":{"title":""}}},"pageContext":{"id":"53933f9f-bd47-51a0-8c64-e0d6eaac35d5","previousPostId":"9bfac51b-cc05-5a99-8941-ecb82f4c4e99","nextPostId":"80eeb5b7-a87b-50b5-a5fe-32c200e49ea7"}},
